.TH KINDLETOOL 1 "July 2026" "KindleTool 1.6.6" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
kindletool \- create, inspect, convert, and safely extract Kindle update packages
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kindletool
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The Rust KindleTool is compatible with the 1.6.6 package formats and command surface.
It recognizes FB01, FB02, FB03, FC02, FC04, FD03, FD04, FL01, SP01, CB01, gzip,
and ZIP headers. Package fields are decoded explicitly as little endian values and
untrusted archive paths are confined to the requested extraction directory.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B md [input] [output]
Apply the Kindle byte substitution. A missing path or a single dash selects standard input or output.
.TP
.B dm [input] [output]
Reverse the Kindle byte substitution.
.TP
.B convert [options] input...
Inspect or convert one or more packages. File-mode conversion deletes each source only after a
validated, flushed, atomic output succeeds. Use
.B -k
to keep sources or
.B -c
to write payloads to standard output and always keep sources.
.TP
.B extract [-u] input output
Validate the complete decoded update archive in private staging and atomically commit it to an
absent or empty output directory.
.TP
.B create type [options] input... output
Create an ota, ota2, recovery, recovery2, or signed userdata package. A single .tar.gz, .tgz,
or .tar input is treated as a prebuilt archive.
.TP
.B info serial
Print the model and derived root/recovery passwords for a 16-character serial number.
.TP
.B version
Print version information.
.TP
.B help [command]
Print general or command-specific help.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B KT_WITH_UNKNOWN_DEVCODES
Expose data-mined device identifiers in aliases and numeric diagnostic output.
.TP
.B KT_PKG_METADATA_DUMP
Write shell-friendly parsed package metadata to this path.
.TP
.B TMPDIR
Select the directory used for temporary package and archive files.
.SH SAFETY
Extraction rejects absolute paths, parent traversal, escaping symbolic or hard links, and paths
whose existing ancestors are symbolic links. It refuses nonempty destinations and leaves no partial
output when validation fails. Package creation never remounts or modifies a Kindle root filesystem.
.SH LICENSE
GPL-3.0-or-later. The C 1.6.6 implementation remains the compatibility oracle.
